Subject: [PATCH 2/9] bridge: complete Phase 1 leaves (config + URL + handle
 pointer)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Ports the remaining five Phase 1 bridge modules from
typescript/src/bridge/ that were deferred from PR #200 because they
either inline cross-folder helpers or use pydantic schema validation
that needed more careful handling.

New modules:
- env_less_bridge_config.py — pydantic v2 schema (strict=True) for
  v2 bridge timing config; matches TS Zod fields/bounds/defaults
- poll_config.py — pydantic v2 schema with cross-field validators
  enforcing the at-capacity liveness invariant (heartbeat > 0 OR
  poll_interval_ms_at_capacity > 0) and the zero-or-≥100 unit-confusion
  rejection; both single-session AND multisession paths covered
- bridge_config.py — env-override helpers (CLAUDE_BRIDGE_OAUTH_TOKEN /
  CLAUDE_BRIDGE_BASE_URL); fallthrough returns None for token and an
  inline production URL constant for base URL (per refactoring plan
  §0.1 Q6, no OAuth keychain port until Phase 2)
- bridge_status_util.py — URL builders, shimmer animation math, status
  state machine, OSC 8 link wrapping; re-exports canonical
  utils/format.format_duration; inlines 3 cross-folder deps
  (truncate_to_width with ANSI-aware grapheme iteration, claude.ai
  base URL, remote session URL with cse_→session_ retag)
- repl_bridge_handle.py — process-global pointer to the active bridge
  handle; multi-peer dedup via concurrent_sessions is a TODO-noop
  with debug-log marker until Phase 2

Extended:
- __init__.py: 20 new re-exports (now 56 total in __all__) covering
  the new modules' consumer-facing surface

91 new tests, all passing. 370/370 bridge tests pass overall.
Legacy test_porting_workspace.py (23 tests) still passes.

ANSI-aware truncate_to_width: SGR / OSC 8 escapes contribute zero
visual width and are kept whole; closing escapes in the tail are
preserved post-truncation so color doesn't bleed into following
terminal output.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
